⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Emmanuel Goldstein
node 1984 · 1984 · ⟦Emmanuel Goldstein:1984:649b12⟧

WHO   — Emmanuel Goldstein — the enemy of the people
WHAT  — The designated hate-object and the (perhaps Party-written) resistance: the focus of the Two Minutes Hate and the bait for would-be rebels.
WHERE — 1984 · 1984  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a regime defines itself by an enemy — and may invent both the enemy and the rebellion that opposes him.
HOW   — By a face for the daily Hate and a Book that explains the system too perfectly to be safe.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the enemy the Party needs — and perhaps the Party wrote me, so that every rebel reads my Book on the way to Room 101.

